<p>
  <i>JJack</i> is an audio driver for the <a href="http://java.sun.com/products/java-media/sound/">Java Sound API</a> and a standalone application programming interface (API)
  for the <a href="http://java.sun.com/">Java programming language</a>
  that allows Java audio applications to use the
  <a href="http://www.jackaudio.org/">JACK Audio Connection Kit</a>:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><b><a href="http://www.jackaudio.org/">JACK</a>-driver</b> for the standard <b>Java Sound API</b> via <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/javax/sound/sampled/spi/MixerProvider.html"><code>javax.sound.sampled.spi.MixerProvider</code></a></li>
  <li>Use Java to create <b>audio processors</b> (effects processors, synthesizers etc.).</li>
  <li><b>JavaBeans-compatible</b> event mechanism to interconnect audio processors.</li>
  <li><b>Native bridge</b> code uses <a href="http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/nio/ByteBuffer.html"><code>java.nio.ByteBuffer</code></a> for efficient direct memory access from Java.</li>
</ul>

